 <title>5 Ways Cities Can Benefit from SunShot’s Latest Solar Prize Challenge</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/eere/articles/5-ways-cities-can-benefit-sunshot-s-latest-solar-prize-challenge</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;The solar industry is growing fast. Despite this rapid growth, solar energy remains inaccessible to nearly half of American households and businesses, as well as many local governments and nonprofits. Cities can now go solar through the Solar in Your Community Challenge, a program launched by U.S. Department of Energy’s SunShot Initiative to expand solar access to those who have been left out of the growing solar market. Five benefits for cities of this challenge include saving money, job growth, helping low-income residents, improving resiliency, and meeting environmental goals.&lt;/p&gt;
